These are my notes from the CSS Tutorial

in the <head> section
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">

'em' is a calculated size (2em = 2x current)

Units:
px, em, pt, %, pc, cm, mm, in

Color specifications:
	red
	rgb(255,0,0)
	rgb(100%,0%,0%)
	#ff0000
	#f00
also: aqua, black, blue, fuchsia, gray, green, lime, maroon, navy, olive, purple, red, silver, teal, white, and yellow. transparent ... + more

font-family:
	This is the font itself, such as "Times New Roman", Arial, or Verdana, helvetica
	(can do: firstchoice, secondchoice)
	(must be in "quotes if" more than one word)
	

font-size

font-weight:
	bold, normal, lighter, bolder, 100, 200,...,900
	
font-style:
	italic, normal, oblique
	
font-variant: 
	small-caps, inherit, normal
	
text-transform:
	capitalize, lowercase, uppercase, etc
	
text-decoration:
	underline (only links), overline, line-through
	
letter-spacing

